(69, NULL, NULL, 'Carrot-Walnut Cake Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4><strong>For the cake</strong>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>275g (10oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Syrup Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>200ml (7floz) sunflower oil</li>\r\n<li>1 large egg</li>\r\n<li>1 large yolk</li>\r\n<li>150g (5oz) carrots, peeled &amp; coarsely grated to yield 125g (4&frac12;oz)</li>\r\n<li>60g (2&frac12;oz) walnuts, roughly chopped</li>\r\n<li>40g (1&frac12;oz) desiccated coconut</li>\r\n<li>a zest of &frac12; medium orange</li>\r\n<li>165g (5&frac12;oz) plain flour</li>\r\n<li>&frac12; rounded tsp baking powder</li>\r\n<li>&frac12; rounded tsp bicarbonate of soda</li>\r\n<li>2 level tsp cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>2 large egg whites</li>\r\n<li>a pinch of salt</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>For the caramelised walnuts</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>20g (&frac34;oz) unsalted butter</li>\r\n<li>40g (1&frac12;oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Syrup Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>75g (3oz) walnut halves</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>For the icing</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>225g (8oz) full-fat cream cheese</li>\r\n<li>95g (3&frac12;oz) unsalted butter, softened</li>\r\n<li>95g (3&frac12;oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Syrup Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>zest of &frac12; medium orange</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp orange juice</li>\r\n<li>3 tsp lemon juice</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You will also need a 20cm (8&rdquo;) springform cake tin, greased and the base lined with parchment paper, plus a piece to cover the cake and some for the caramelised walnuts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt;" lang="EN-US"> <!--EndFragment--></span></p>\r\n\r\n<!--EndFragment-->', NULL),
(70, NULL, NULL, 'Carrot-Walnut Cake Nutritional Information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Nutrition Values per serving</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Women`s GDA per serving</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Typical GDA Values (Women)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Energy&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(cal)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>866</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>43.3%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Energy&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(kj)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>3637</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>N/A</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Protein (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>1.3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>2.9%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Carbohydrates (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>72.5</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>31.5%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>of which sugars (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>53.3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>59.2%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Fat (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>63.5</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>90.5%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Of which saturated fat (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>20.0</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>100.0%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Fibre (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>28.3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>118.0%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>24g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Salt (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>0.8</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>13.2%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>6g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(71, NULL, NULL, 'Carrot-Walnut Cake Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 170&deg;C/Fan150&deg;C, 325&deg;F, Gas Mark 3.</li>\r\n<li>Pour the oil into the bowl of an electric mixer, add the&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Syrup Cane Sugar&nbsp;and beat briefly until combined on a medium speed. Reduce the speed down to low, add the egg and the yolk, followed by the carrots, walnuts, coconut and orange zest.</li>\r\n<li>Sift together the flour, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda and cinnamon, add to the mixing bowl and briefly mix in just enough to combine, scraping down the sides. Tip into a large bowl, then wash up the mixer bowl, ensuring it is completely dry and clean. Add the whites and salt and whisk until firm peaks form. Using a large metal spoon, carefully and lightly fold in 1 spoonful of the egg white into the cake mixture to loosen it, then add the rest.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(72, NULL, NULL, 'Chocolate Swirl Meringues instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/Fan180&deg;, 400&deg;F, Gas Mark 6.</li>\r\n<li>Tip the&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Caster Cane Sugar&nbsp;onto one of the baking trays and spread it out in an even layer. Warm through on the middle shelf of the oven for about 5-6 minutes or until the cane sugar feels hot to touch and is lightly coloured, stirring once. Don&rsquo;t let it caramelize. Pour into a small bowl.</li>\r\n<li>Turn the oven heat down to its lowest, around 110&deg;C/Fan90&deg;C, 225&deg;F, Gas Mark &frac14;.</li>\r\n<li>As soon as the&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Caster Cane Sugar&nbsp;is ready, using an electric mixer, add the whites to the bowl and whisk at high speed until they are light and foamy, for about 1 minute. Slowly add the hot&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Caster Cane Sugar, a dessert spoon at a time, and continue whisking until the mixture has cooled and is very thick and glossy. Scrape down the sides halfway through. This will take about 10 minutes.</li>\r\n<li>Sift the cocoa over the meringue mixture and, using a large spoon, carefully fold it through using 3 or 4 strokes so that it looks marbled.</li>\r\n<li>Use a little of the meringue to stick down the parchment paper on the remaining 2 baking trays. With 2 large spoons, divide the mixture into 10 large dollops, spacing them well apart on the trays as they almost double in size when baking.</li>\r\n<li>Bake on the middle and top shelves of the oven for 1&frac34;-2 hours, swapping the trays over halfway through. The meringues are ready when they are crisp on the outsides, the insides are still soft, and they sound hollow when the bottoms are tapped. Remove to a wire rack to cool, then store in an air-tight container.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(73, NULL, NULL, 'Chocolate Swirl Meringues Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>295g (10&frac12;oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Caster Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>5 large egg whites, about 150g (5oz)</li>\r\n<li>2 rounded tbsp cocoa powder</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You will also need 3 large baking trays lined with parchment paper.</p>', NULL),
