>0.2</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>3.6%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>6g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(78, NULL, NULL, 'Sneak a peek into our baking world Top text', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<p>Introducing Lorna Wing, our expert food consultant who is the brains behind our new Taste Experience range of golden and brown cane sugars.</p>', NULL),
(79, NULL, NULL, 'Introducing Lorna Wing', 1, 'page', 1, 0, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<p>It feels like I&rsquo;ve always been in the kitchen. Growing up as one of five girls, help was always expected and appreciated. Whether it was rustling up packet-mix Viota teacakes after Sunday school or helping make the morning porridge, I was my mother&rsquo;s willing, albeit Lilliputian, sous-chef. In the years since, I cooked my way around the world from Monaco to Malta, and the States to South Africa, then sailed the Atlantic, crewing aboard a yacht bound for the West Indies. A restaurant for Sir Terence Conran followed, then a bit of book-writing, plus a ground-breaking catering company organising glam events in the grandest of palaces, castles and the like. Next, a 10-year stint with Queen Delia at Sainsbury&rsquo;s Magazine, who taught me the art of photo shoots and super-accurate recipe testing and writing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Now, I do lots of food consulting. So all that cooking, eating and testing along the way stood me in good stead when, last spring, Tate &amp; Lyle Sugars asked me to work with them on their new Taste Experience range of golden and brown cane sugars inspired from around the world. Always on a sugar quest as a child, be it my youngest sister&rsquo;s much-coveted sweets, the jelly cubes in the larder or a stubby finger dipped into Lyle&rsquo;s iconic tin of molten golden syrup, this was a dream job.</p>', NULL),
