(124, NULL, NULL, 'Sugar-dusted grilled nectarines with meringue ice cream Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Make the meringues first. Preheat the oven to 110&deg;C/Fan90&deg;C, 225&deg;F, Gas Mark &frac12;.</li>\r\n<li>Whisk the egg white and salt together in a mixing bowl with an electric hand mixer at high speed until stiff but not dry. Slowly add the cane sugar, a little at a time, beating well after each addition until thick and glossy. Spoon the meringue mixture onto the baking tray to make about 12 small blobs, spacing them a little apart.</li>\r\n<li>Bake on the middle shelf of the oven for 1&frac12;-2 hours, then switch off the oven and leave them overnight. The outsides will be softly sticky whilst the insides will be dry.</li>\r\n<li>Lightly whip the cream in a bowl until soft peaks form, then break the meringue into chunks and fold into the cream. Transfer to a small lidded container and freeze for 2 hours until very firm, then divide into 4 rough scoops and return to the freezer.</li>\r\n<li>Preheat the grill.</li>\r\n<li>Meanwhile, halve the fruits and remove the stones. Arrange the fruit in the ovenproof dishes, brush the cut sides with the melted butter, sprinkle with the cane sugar and grill for about 8 minutes or until they start to caramelise. Top each one with the meringue ice cream, scatter over the blackberries and grill again for about 1 minute until the ice cream just starts to melt. Serve immediately.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(125, NULL, NULL, 'Sugar-dusted grilled nectarines with meringue ice cream Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4 class="Section1"><strong>for the meringue ice cream</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>50g (2oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Dark Soft Brown</li>\r\n<li>1 medium egg white, room temperature</li>\r\n<li>a pinch of salt</li>\r\n<li>cane sugar</li>\r\n<li>200ml (7floz) double cream</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 class="Section1"><strong>for the fruit</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>40g (1&frac12;oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Dark Soft Brown cane sugar</li>\r\n<li>4 ripe nectarines or peaches</li>\r\n<li>4 ripe plums</li>\r\n<li>40g (1&frac12;oz) unsalted butter, melted</li>\r\n<li>110g (4oz) blackberries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="Section1">You will also need a baking tray lined with parchment and 4 small shallow ovenproof dishes.</p>', NULL),
