(133, NULL, NULL, 'Triple chocolate hazelnut cookies Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Roughly chop all the chocolate into smallish chunks.</li>\r\n<li>Combine the butter and&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Light Muscovado Cane Sugar&nbsp;together in a mixing bowl and, using a wooden spoon, beat until light and creamy for 2-3 minutes. Mix in the egg and vanilla and scrape down the sides of the bowl.</li>\r\n<li>Next, sift together the flour, bicarbonate of soda, baking powder and salt then stir into the creamed mixture to make a soft dough.</li>\r\n<li>Add the chocolate and nuts and mix through. Divide into 16, roll into balls, place on a tray, cover with cling film and chill for 30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/Fan160&deg;C, 350F, Gas Mark 4.</li>\r\n<li>Place 3 or 4 balls of dough on each baking tray, well spaced apart as they will spread. Bake on the top and middle shelves of the oven for 20-22 minutes, swapping the trays over halfway through. They are ready when pale golden and still a little soft. Leave to firm up on the trays before removing with a palette knife to a wire rack to cool, then bake the rest of the cookies. Serve.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(134, NULL, NULL, 'Triple chocolate hazelnut cookies Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>330g (11&frac12;oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Light Muscovado Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>100g (3&frac12;oz) dark chocolate, minimum 70% cocoa solids</li>\r\n<li>100g (3&frac12; oz) milk chocolate</li>\r\n<li>100g (3&frac12;oz) white chocolate</li>\r\n<li>200g (7oz) unsalted butter, softened</li>\r\n<li>1 large egg</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li>\r\n<li>330g (11&frac12;oz) plain flour</li>\r\n<li>&frac34; level tsp bicarbonate of soda</li>\r\n<li>1 level tsp baking powder</li>\r\n<li>&frac12; level tsp salt</li>\r\n<li>100g (3&frac12;oz) blanched hazelnuts, roughly chopped</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="Section1">You will also need 2 baking trays lined with parchment paper.</p>', NULL),
(135, NULL, NULL, 'Triple chocolate hazelnut cookies Nutritional Information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Values per serving</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Women`s GDA per serving</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Typical GDA Values (Women)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Energy (kcal)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>390</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>19.5%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Energy (kJ)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>1638</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>N/A</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Protein (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>5.0</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>11.1%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Carbohydrates (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>46.6</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>20.2%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>of which sugars (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>28.4</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>31.6%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Fat (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>20.7</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>29.6%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Of which saturated fat (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>10.4</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>52.0%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Fibre (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>2.2</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>9.2%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>24g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Salt (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>0.5</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>7.9%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>6g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(136, NULL, NULL, 'Victoria Sandwich Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/160&deg;Fan/Gas 4.</li>\r\n<li>In a large bowl mix the butter and Tate &amp; Lye Fairtrade Golden Caster Cane Sugar together with an electric hand mixer until soft and creamy for about 1 minute, then beat in the eggs a little at a time. Sift over the flour and baking powder, lightly fold in with a metal spoon and add the milk to make a soft consistency which will easily drop from the spoon.</li>\r\n<li>Spoon the mixture into the cake tins and level out.</li>\r\n<li>Bake on the middle shelf of the oven for 25 minutes until golden brown, well risen and the cakes spring back when lightly pressed with a finger.</li>\r\n<li>Leave to cool for 20 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely and discard the parchment.</li>\r\n<li>Lightly whip the cream in a bowl until soft peaks form.</li>\r\n<li>Sandwich the cakes together first with the jam, then with the whipped cream and arrange on a plate. Dust with a little Tate &amp; Lye Fairtrade Golden Caster Cane Sugar and serve.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(137, NULL, NULL, 'Victoria Sandwich Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>for the cake</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>225g (8oz) Tate &amp; Lye Fairtrade Golden Caster Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>225g (8oz) unsalted butter, softened</li>\r\n<li>4 large eggs, beaten</li>\r\n<li>225g (8oz) self-raising flour</li>\r\n<li>1 rounded tsp baking powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp milk</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>for the filling &amp; decoration</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tate &amp; Lye Fairtrade Golden Caster Cane Sugar, for sprinkling</li>\r\n<li>150ml (5floz) double cream</li>\r\n<li>5 rounded tbsp raspberry jam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You will also need 2 x 20cm (8&rdquo;) deep sandwich tins, greased and the bases lined with parchment paper.</p>', NULL),
(138, NULL, NULL, 'Victoria Sandwich Nutritional Information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">474</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">23.7%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">1978</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">5.9</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">13.1%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">46.8</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">20.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">29.9</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">33.2%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">29.9</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">42.7%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">17.7</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">88.5%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.8</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">3.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.466</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">7.8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(139, NULL, NULL, 'Strawberry & Cream trifles Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Make the syllabub first. Mix the lemon juice, brandy, wine and Tate &amp; Lyle Golden Syrup Cane Sugar in a bowl. In another bowl, lightly whisk the cream until it just starts to thicken, then, little by little, whisk in the wine mixture until soft peaks form.</li>\r\n<li>Combine the cream, Tate &amp; Lyle Golden Syrup Cane Sugar and vanilla in a bowl and lightly whisk until soft peaks form.</li>\r\n<li>Put the strawberries, Tate &amp; Lyle Golden Syrup Cane Sugar and lemon juice in a food processor and blend until pur&eacute;ed then pass through a sieve set over a bowl.</li>\r\n<li>Stamp out 16 circles from the brioche with the cutters then sprinkle over the wine. Reserve 24 sliced strawberries for decoration, and then arrange half of the rest of the strawberries in the bottom of 8 small glass bowls and drizzle over half of the sauce. Place a brioche slice on top, then spoon on the vanilla cream, lightly spreading to the edges. Repeat with another layer of strawberries, sauce and brioche. Top with the syllabub, spreading it to the edges, decorate with the reserved strawberry slices and serve.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(140, NULL, NULL, 'Strawberry & Cream trifles Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>for the syllabub</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>3 tsp lemon juice</li>\r\n<li>3 tsp brandy</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsp sweet white wine</li>\r\n<li>1&frac12; rounded tbsp Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Syrup Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>125ml (4floz) double cream</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>for the vanilla cream</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>150ml (5floz) double cream</li>\r\n<li>25g (1oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Syrup Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>for the strawberry sauce (makes 150ml)</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>225g (8oz) strawberries, hulled</li>\r\n<li>3 rounded tbsp Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Syrup Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp lemon juice</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>for the trifle</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>16 brioche slices</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsp sweet white wine</li>\r\n<li>350g (12oz) strawberries, hulled &amp; thinly sliced</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You will also need some plain cutters to fit the size of bowls you are using.</p>', NULL),
