(178, NULL, NULL, 'Chocolate salami Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>First, rub the pistachios between your hands to remove any loose pieces of skin.</li>\r\n<li>Next, melt the butter in a pan over a low heat, add the&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Dark Muscovado Cane Sugar&nbsp;and stir to dissolve for 2-3 minutes stirring all the time until the mixture begins to bubble. Remove from the heat, stir in the cocoa until smooth, tip into a mixing bowl and leave to cool.</li>\r\n<li>Beat the eggs in a small bowl, then, to remove the thready bits, strain through a sieve set over the mixing bowl. Add the vanilla and orange liqueur and stir well, before adding the biscuits, pistachios, pecans, peel and cranberries and mix thoroughly.</li>\r\n<li>Divide in half and spoon onto 2x45cm (18&rdquo;) lengths of clingfilm. Roll evenly into a salami shape, about 23cm (9&rdquo;) long. Twist the ends of the clingfilm to secure and chill in the fridge for 6-8 hours to firm up.</li>\r\n<li>Remove the clingfilm from the chocolate salamis, put on to a tray and lightly dust with&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar. Slice, arrange on a plate and serve.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4>Note:</h4>\r\n<p>This recipe contains raw eggs.</p>', NULL),
(179, NULL, NULL, 'Chocolate salami Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>150g (5oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Dark Muscovado Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>50g (2oz) unsalted shelled pistachio nuts</li>\r\n<li>110g (4oz) unsalted butter</li>\r\n<li>75g (3oz) cocoa powder, sifted</li>\r\n<li>2 large eggs</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp vanilla extract</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp orange liqueur</li>\r\n<li>225g (8oz) digestive biscuits, broken into smallish pieces</li>\r\n<li>50g (2oz) pecan nuts, halved</li>\r\n<li>110g (4oz) mixed peel</li>\r\n<li>110g (4oz) dried cranberries</li>\r\n<li>Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar, to dust</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(180, NULL, NULL, 'Chocolate salami Nutritional Information', 1, 'page', 0, 4, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Nutrition Values per serving</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>GDA per serving (based on Women&rsquo;s GDA)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Typical GDA Values (Women)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Energy (kcal)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>111</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>5.6%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Energy (kJ)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>466</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>N/A</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Protein (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>1.3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>2.9%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Carbohydrates (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>14.9</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>0.4%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>of which sugars (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>10.6</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>11.8%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Fat (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>5.4</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>7.7%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Of which saturated fat (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>2.0</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>10.0%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Fibre (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>0.7</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>2.9%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>24g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Salt (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>0.2</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>3.1%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>6g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(181, NULL, NULL, 'Honeyed Carrot Cake Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/160&deg;Fan/Gas 4.</li>\r\n<li>In a large mixing bowl whisk the oil and Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Granulated Cane Sugar&nbsp;together, then beat in the eggs. Sift over the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg and lightly fold in with a metal spoon until smooth.</li>\r\n<li>Stir in the carrots, walnuts, raisins and orange zest.</li>\r\n<li>Pour the mixture into the cake tin and bake on the middle shelf of the oven for 55-60 minutes or until golden brown and a fine skewer comes out clean when poked in the middle. Cool for 30 minutes in the tin then turn out onto a wire rack, remove the parchment and leave to cool completely.</li>\r\n<li>Sift the Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar into a bowl and stir in the orange juice to make a slightly thickened icing. Pour over the cake, scatter with walnuts, lightly dust with a little Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar, arrange on a plate and serve.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(182, NULL, NULL, 'Honeyed Carrot Cake Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>for the cake</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>150g (5oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Golden Granulated Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>150ml (5floz) sunflower oil</li>\r\n<li>3 large eggs</li>\r\n<li>150g (5oz) self-raising flour</li>\r\n<li>1 rounded tsp baking powder</li>\r\n<li>1 rounded tsp cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>large pinch nutmeg</li>\r\n<li>250g (9oz) carrots, peeled &amp; coarsely grated</li>\r\n<li>50g (2oz) walnut pieces</li>\r\n<li>50g (2oz) raisins</li>\r\n<li>1 medium orange, zested</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>for the icing &amp; decoration</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>110g (4oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar, plus extra for dusting</li>\r\n<li>1&frac12; tbsp orange juice</li>\r\n<li>25g (1oz) walnut pieces</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You will also need a 23cm (9&rdquo;) loaf tin, greased and the base lined with parchment paper.</p>', NULL),
(183, NULL, NULL, 'Honeyed Carrot Cake Nutritional Information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">399</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">20.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">1413</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">5.3</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">11.8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">44.3</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">19.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">32.8</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">36.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">22.8</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">32.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">3.0</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">15.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">3.3</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">13.8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.394</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">6.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(184, NULL, NULL, 'SCONES Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Pre-heat the oven to 200&deg;C/Fan180/400&deg;F/Gas 6</li>\r\n<li>Sift the flour and baking powder into a bowl then rub in the butter with your fingertips until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Stir in the Tate &amp; Lyle&nbsp;Fairtrade&nbsp;Caster Cane Sugar and mix well.</li>\r\n<li>Make a well in the centre, pour in the milk and mix to a soft elastic dough.</li>\r\n<li>Knead lightly on a floured surface and pat out to about 2cm (&frac34;&rdquo;) thickness. Using a 5cm (2&rdquo;) plain or fluted biscuit cutter, dip into a bowl of flour then stamp into rounds, placing them on a lightly greased baking sheet.</li>\r\n<li>Gather up the trimmings and cut out more rounds. Brush with the beaten egg or milk for a glossy finish or sprinkle with a little flour for a soft finish.</li>\r\n<li>Bake for 12-14 minutes until well risen and golden brown. Leave to cool on a wire rack then serve warm, split and spread with butter or cream and jam.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(185, NULL, NULL, 'SCONES Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>225g plain flour</li>\r\n<li>3 tsp baking powder</li>\r\n<li>50g unsalted butter, cubed</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Caster Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>120ml milk</li>\r\n<li>beaten egg, milk or flour, to finish</li>\r\n<li>butter, whipped or clotted cream and strawberry/raspberry jam</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(186, NULL, NULL, 'SCONES Nutritional Information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">343</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">17.2%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">1440</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">5.3</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">11.8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">47.2</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">20.5%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">13.9</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">15.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">16.0</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">22.9%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">9.8</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">49.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">1.4</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">5.8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.782</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">13.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(187, NULL, NULL, 'ALMOND SHORTBREAD instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 170&deg;C/Fan150&deg;/325&deg;F/Gas 3.</li>\r\n<li>Beat the butter and almond extract in a mixing bowl until soft. Gradually beat in the Tate &amp; Lyle&nbsp;Fairtrade&nbsp;Caster Cane Sugar.</li>\r\n<li>Add the ground almonds and semolina, then sift in the flour. Stir well, then work together with your hands to make a smooth dough. &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Grease a shallow 28x18cm/11x7in oblong tin and press the shortbread dough into it, in an even layer. Pick all over with a fork and scatter over the flaked almonds.</li>\r\n<li>Bake for 45 minutes until pale golden. With a sharp knife mark into fingers and allow to cool in the tin. Cut up when cold and serve dusted with the cinnamon and Tate &amp; Lyle&nbsp;Fairtrade&nbsp;Icing Cane Sugar.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(188, NULL, NULL, 'ALMOND SHORTBREAD ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>For the shortbread</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>225g unsalted butter</li>\r\n<li>225g plain flour</li>\r\n<li>115g Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Caster Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>100g ground almonds</li>\r\n<li>50g semolina</li>\r\n<li>20g flaked almonds</li>\r\n<li>Few drops almond extract</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>to dust</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>1tsp ground cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>1tbsp Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(189, NULL, NULL, 'ALMOND SHORTBREAD  nutritional information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl22">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl23">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl23">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl23">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">208</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">10.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl23">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">867</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl23">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">2.7</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">6.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl23">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">19.2</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">8.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl23">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">7.7</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">8.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl23">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">13.6</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">19.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl23">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">6.8</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">34.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl23">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">1.0</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">4.2%</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl23">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">0.006</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">0.1%</td>\r\n<td class="xl22">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(190, NULL, NULL, 'EASTER BISCUITS  instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Pre-heat the oven to 180&deg;C/Fan160&deg;C/350&deg;F/Gas 4. Grease two baking sheets.<br /> Put the butter and Tate &amp; Lyle&nbsp;Fairtrade Light&nbsp;Soft Brown Cane Sugar into a bowl and beat together until light and fluffy.</li>\r\n<li>Beat in the egg and milk, and stir in the mixed peel and currants.<br />Sift in the flour and spice and mix together to make a firm dough. Knead lightly until smooth.</li>\r\n<li>Roll out the dough to 5mm (&frac14;&rdquo;) thick and stamp out with the cutters. Place them on the baking sheets and bake for 12-15 minutes, swapping the trays over hallway through, until golden brown. Remove the biscuits from the oven and transfer to a wire rack to cool</li>\r\n<li>Sift the Tate &amp; Lyle&nbsp;Fairtrade Fondant&nbsp;Icing Cane Sugar into a bowl and mix to a smooth paste with enough water to make a stiff but just spreadable icing. Divide between four bowls and add the smallest amount of each food colouring to create a pastel shade. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Carefully spread over the biscuits and place a sliver ball for eyes before the icing sets.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(191, NULL, NULL, 'EASTER BISCUITS  ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>For the biscuits</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>350g plain flour</li>\r\n<li>175g Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Light Soft Brown Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>150g unsalted butter, softened</li>\r\n<li>1 large egg, beaten</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp milk</li>\r\n<li>50g mixed peel, finely chopped</li>\r\n<li>75g currants</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp mixed spice</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>for the decoration:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>500g Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Fondant Icing Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>pink, yellow, blue &amp; green food colouring</li>\r\n<li>silver balls</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You will also need some Easter-shaped cutters &ndash; chicks, rabbits and eggs.</p>', NULL),
(192, NULL, NULL, 'EASTER BISCUITS nutritional information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">181</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">9.1%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">764</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">1.5</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">3.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">34.2</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">14.9%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">25.3</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">28.1%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">4.6</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">6.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">2.7</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">13.5%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.5</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">2.1%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.024</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">0.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(193, NULL, NULL, 'ALMOND SYRUP TART  instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/Fan180&deg;C/400&deg;F/Gas 6.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Roll out the pastry on a lightly floured surface and use to line a 20cm (8&rdquo;) round fluted flan tin, trimming off any excess.</li>\r\n<li>Prick the base and sides with a fork then spread over 2 tbsp of the Lyle&rsquo;s Golden Syrup and chill in a refrigerator whilst making the filling.</li>\r\n<li>In a bowl beat together the almonds, Tate &amp; Lyle&nbsp;Fairtrade&nbsp;Caster Cane Sugar, the rest of the Lyle&rsquo;s Golden Syrup, butter, eggs and almond extract until well mixed and smooth.</li>\r\n<li>Spoon the filling over the pastry base and smooth over the surface. Place in the preheated oven and bake for 20 minutes, reduce the temperature to 180&deg;C/1Fan60&deg;C /350/&deg;F/Gas 4 and continue to cook for a further 25 minutes or until the filling is set and golden, cover with foil if the top is getting too brown. Remove and serve hot or cold dredged with a little Tate &amp; Lyle&nbsp;Fairtrade&nbsp;Icing Cane Sugar.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(194, NULL, NULL, 'ALMOND SYRUP TART ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>225g shortcrust pastry, thawed if frozen</li>\r\n<li>200g ground almonds</li>\r\n<li>50g Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Caster Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>50g unsalted butter, beaten</li>\r\n<li>4tbsp Lyle&rsquo;s Golden Syrup&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>3 medium eggs, beaten</li>\r\n<li>&frac12; tsp almond extract</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>To decorate</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
