(223, NULL, NULL, 'SIZZLING BEEF WRAPS instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Combine all the ingredients for the salsa, place in a small bowl, cover lightly and reserve for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavours to blend and develop.</li>\r\n<li>Place the steak strips in a shallow dish then blend the soy sauce with the Tate &amp; Lyle Dark Soft Brown Cane Sugar, the chillies, garlic, lime rind and juice with the oil and pour over the steak. Cover loosely then leave to marinate in the fridge for at least 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>\r\n<li>When ready to cook, drain off the marinade and reserve. Heat 2 tablespoons of the marinade in a large frying pan or wok, add the spring onions and quickly cook for 5 minutes. Add the pepper strips and continue to cook quickly for a further 4 minutes or until the onions and peppers are cooked but still retain a bit of crunch. Remove and reserve.</li>\r\n<li>Add 1-2 tablespoons of the marinade to the pan or wok and quickly cook the steak for 3-5 minutes or until cooked to taste.</li>\r\n<li>Return the onion and peppers to the pan with a further tablespoon of the marinade, turn the heat up high and cook for 1-2 minutes or until sizzling.</li>\r\n<li>Heat the tortillas, according to manufacturer&rsquo;s instructions, then fill with the prepared steak filling, top with the salsa, and serve with the soured cream and limes.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(224, NULL, NULL, 'SIZZLING BEEF WRAPS ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>for the salsa</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>175g ripe tomatoes, skinned, deseeded &amp; finely chopped</li>\r\n<li>1 garlic clove, peeled &amp; crushed</li>\r\n<li>1-2 red chillies, deseeded &amp; finely chopped</li>\r\n<li>4 spring onions, trimmed &amp; finely chopped</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tsp Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Dark Soft Brown Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp freshly chopped coriander</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>for the wraps:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>350g sirloin or rump steak, trimmed &amp; cut into strips</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp soy sauce</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Dark Soft Brown Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>1-2 red chillies, deseeded &amp; &nbsp;chopped</li>\r\n<li>3-4 garlic cloves, peeled &amp; chopped</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp grated lime zest&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsp lime juice</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp olive oil</li>\r\n<li>1 large onion, peeled &amp; thickly sliced</li>\r\n<li>1 large red pepper, deseeded &amp; cut into strips</li>\r\n<li>6 wheat tortillas</li>\r\n<li>soured cream, to serve</li>\r\n<li>lime wedges, to garnish&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(225, NULL, NULL, 'SIZZLING BEEF WRAPS nutritional information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl30">423</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">21.2%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl31">1771</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">26.1</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">58.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">44.4</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">19.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">12.8</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">14.2%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">15.7</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">22.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">5.4</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">27.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">3.8</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">15.8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">1.690</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">28.2%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(226, NULL, NULL, 'Seared Citrus Chicken instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Place the chicken in a shallow dish. Blend the Tate &amp; Lyle Light Soft Brown Cane Sugar with the oil, lemon juice and crushed chillies or chilli powder and seasoning, then pour over the chicken.</li>\r\n<li>Add the oregano sprigs. Cover loosely then allow to marinade in the fridge for at least 30 minutes. Turn the breasts at least once during this time.</li>\r\n<li>When ready to cook, drain the chicken breasts, reserving the marinade. If using a griddle pan, heat the lightly oiled pan then add the chicken and seal on both sides. Add the marinade and cook for 15 minutes or until the chicken is thoroughly cooked.</li>\r\n<li>If using a frying pan, heat 1 extra tablespoon oil, add the chicken and cook over a high heat until sealed. Add the marinade then continue to cook the chicken for 15 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, make sure the marinade does not completely dry up and burn.</li>\r\n<li>Season to taste then serve with the vegetables and garnish with the grilled orange wedges. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4>NOTE:</h4>\r\n<p>Chicken can also be cooked on the barbecue, brushing occasionally with the marinade.</p>', NULL),
(227, NULL, NULL, 'Seared Citrus Chicken ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, each about 150g</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Light Soft Brown Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsp olive oil</li>\r\n<li>90ml lemon juice</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp crushed chillies or chilli powder</li>\r\n<li>salt &amp; freshly ground black pepper</li>\r\n<li>a few sprigs of oregano</li>\r\n<li>new potatoes and vegetables, to serve</li>\r\n<li>griddled orange wedges, to garnish</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(228, NULL, NULL, 'Seared Citrus Chicken nutritional information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl31">373</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">18.7%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl30">1561</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">44.8</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">99.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">7.5</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">3.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">7.5</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">8.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">18.4</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">26.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">1.6</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">8.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">0.1</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">0.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">0.573</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">9.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(229, NULL, NULL, 'Plum & Almond Tart instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Line a shallow roasting tin 21Cmx30Cm (8 &frac12;&rdquo; x 12&rdquo;) with a parchment paper.</li>\r\n<li>Make the pastry by putting the flour, butter and Tate &amp; Lyle Icing cane sugar into a food processor and blend until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Slowly add the egg and turn off as soon as the mixture forms into a ball. Turn onto a lightly floured surface and roll out the pastry to a rectangle.&nbsp; Place the tin on top of the pastry to judge how much to roll out and Cut out the pastry using the tin as a guide.</li>\r\n<li>Lay the pastry in the tin and press into the edges, and chill for 20 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Pre-heat the oven to 190C/170Cfan/gas 5.</li>\r\n<li>Prick the base of the pastry with a fork, line with foil and bake for 15 minutes. Remove from the oven and reduce the heat to 180C/160Cfan/gas 4.</li>\r\n<li>To make the filling, put the butter and Tate &amp; Lyle Light Soft Brown cane sugar into a food processor and blend until pale and soft. Add the almond extract, eggs, ground almonds and flour and blend well. Spread on top of the pastry then arrange the plums skin side up. Bake for 45 minutes until the filling is golden. Cool and dust with some Tate &amp; Lyle Icing cane sugar before serving.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4>TIP:</h4>\r\n<p>Use other fresh seasonal fruits such an apricots, raspberries, or blackberries instead of the&nbsp;plums.</p>', NULL),
(230, NULL, NULL, 'Plum & Almond Tart ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>For the pastry</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>200g plain flour</li>\r\n<li>100g unsalted butter, cubed</li>\r\n<li>50g Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>1 medium egg, beaten</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>For the filling</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>150g unsalted butter</li>\r\n<li>150g Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Light Soft Brown Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>Few drops almond extract</li>\r\n<li>2 medium eggs, beaten</li>\r\n<li>150g ground almonds</li>\r\n<li>50g plain flour</li>\r\n<li>500g English plums, halved or quartered if large and stoned</li>\r\n<li>Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar, to dust</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
