(250, NULL, NULL, 'Traffic Light Biscuits instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/350&deg;F/Gas 4.</li>\r\n<li>Cream the butter, Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Caster Cane Sugar and Lyle&rsquo;s Golden Syrup together in a bowl until pale and fluffy. Gradually beat in the egg and vanilla essence until well mixed.</li>\r\n<li>Sift together the flour and baking powder and stir into the mixture until it resembles breadcrumbs. Then gather the mixture together with your hands to form a dough.</li>\r\n<li>Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead gently until smooth. Wrap in cling film and chill in the fridge for at least 30 minutes until firm.</li>\r\n<li>Roll out the chilled dough to 3mm (1/8 &rdquo;) thick and cut into rectangles measuring about 3cm x 8.5cm (1&frac14;&rdquo;x3&frac12; &ldquo;).</li>\r\n<li>Using a very small plain round cutter or the end of a 5cm (&frac12; &ldquo;) plain round piping nozzle cut out 3 holes to represent the lights in half of the rectangles only.</li>\r\n<li>Place the rectangles on 2 baking trays lined with parchment paper. Bake for 8-10 minutes or until just golden. Carefully transfer to a wire rack to cool.</li>\r\n<li>Spoon 3 small blobs of the different coloured jams along the centre of the plain biscuits to represent the traffic lights. Dust the biscuits with the holes with a little Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar&nbsp;and then arrange on top of the jam-topped biscuits. Press down gently so that the jam shows through.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(251, NULL, NULL, 'Traffic Light Biscuits ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>For the biscuits</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>100g /4oz unsalted butter, softened</li>\r\n<li>75g /3oz Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Caster Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>25g /1oz Lyle&rsquo;s Golden Syrup</li>\r\n<li>1 large egg, beaten</li>\r\n<li>a few drops vanilla essence</li>\r\n<li>275g /10oz plain flour, sifted</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp baking powder</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>To decorate</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>raspberry jam</li>\r\n<li>pineapple jam</li>\r\n<li>lime marmalade</li>\r\n<li>Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar, to dust</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(252, NULL, NULL, 'Traffic Light Biscuits nutritional information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">169</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">8.5%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">731</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">2.5</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">5.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">27.1</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">11.8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">12.0</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">13.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6.6</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">9.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">3.9</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">19.5%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.6</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">2.5%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">0.144</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">2.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(253, NULL, NULL, 'CINNAMON SPICE LOAF MADE WITH FRUIT SUGAR   instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 170&deg;C/Fan150&deg;C/Gas 3.</li>\r\n<li>Grease and line a 2 lb loaf tin.</li>\r\n<li>Sift the dry ingredients into a bowl, tip the bran from the wholemeal flour left in the sieve into the bowl. Cut the butter into small pieces then add to the bowl and rub into the dry ingredients until the mixture is like fine crumbs.</li>\r\n<li>Stir in the Tate &amp; Lyle Fruit Sugar and sultanas. Beat the eggs with the milk, add to the mixture and stir together to make a soft dropping consistency. Turn into the loaf tin.</li>\r\n<li>Bake in the oven for approximately 1 hour until the loaf is golden and firm to the touch. Test with a skewer which should come out clean. Remove from the oven. Turn the cake onto a wire rack to cool.</li>\r\n<li>Serve sliced and buttered if wished.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(254, NULL, NULL, 'CINNAMON SPICE LOAF MADE WITH FRUIT SUGAR  ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>240ml milk&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>175g plain wholemeal flour</li>\r\n<li>115g unsalted butter&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>175g sultanas</li>\r\n<li>150g Tate &amp; Lyle Fruit Sugar</li>\r\n<li>150g plain flour</li>\r\n<li>2 large eggs&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp baking powder</li>\r\n<li>&frac12; tsp bicarbonate of soda</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp ground cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>&frac12; tsp freshly grated nutmeg</li>\r\n<li>a good pinch of ground cloves</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(255, NULL, NULL, 'CINNAMON SPICE LOAF MADE WITH FRUIT SUGAR  nutritional information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">266</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">13.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">1118</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">5.4</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">12.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">40.4</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">17.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl29">24.0</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">26.7%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">10.1</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">14.4%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">5.7</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">28.5%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">1.9</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">7.9%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">0.380</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">6.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(256, NULL, NULL, 'Duo Dark & White Chocolate Brownies instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/Fan160&deg;C /350&deg;F/Gas 4.</li>\r\n<li>Lightly grease a shallow 23cm (9&rdquo;) square tin and line the base with parchment paper.</li>\r\n<li>Melt the chocolate and butter together in a mixing bowl set over a saucepan of simmering water, making sure the bottom of the bowl doesn&rsquo;t touch the water.</li>\r\n<li>When melted, remove the bowl from the heat, cool a little and stir in the eggs, Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Dark Soft Brown Cane Sugar, flour, cocoa, hazelnuts and chocolate chips, until evenly mixed.</li>\r\n<li>Spoon the mixture into the tin and spread level. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until springy in the centre. Allow to cool for 15 minutes then cut into 16 equal pieces and when cool, remove from the tin.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Dust with the Tate &amp; Lye Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(257, NULL, NULL, 'Duo Dark & White Chocolate Brownies ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>100g plain chocolate, chopped</li>\r\n<li>115g unsalted butter</li>\r\n<li>2 large eggs, beaten</li>\r\n<li>200g Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Dark Soft Brown Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>115g self-raising flour</li>\r\n<li>25g cocoa powder</li>\r\n<li>50g toasted hazelnuts, roughly chopped</li>\r\n<li>100g white chocolate chips</li>\r\n<li>Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(258, NULL, NULL, 'Duo Dark & White Chocolate Brownies nutritional information', 1, 'page', 0, 4, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Nutrition Values per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25">Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">235</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">11.8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">983</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">3.3</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">7.3%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">27.1</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">11.8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">21.5</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">23.9%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">13</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">18.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6.6</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">33.0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">1.1</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">4.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.155</td>\r\n<td class="xl26">2.6%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(259, NULL, NULL, 'Chilled LEMON SOUFFLÃ instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>First prepare the souffl&eacute; dish, 900ml (1&frac12;) pint capacity. Cut a double strip of non-stick parchment paper, long enough to fit around the dish and deep enough to stand about 7.5cm (3&rdquo;) above the top. Secure with sticky tape or tie tightly with string, making sure the paper is held firmly against the dish. Alternatively, prepare 6 individual souffl&eacute; dishes in the same way. Stand on a flat plate or tray.</li>\r\n<li>Finely grate the zest from the lemons and put into a large bowl.</li>\r\n<li>Squeeze the juice and strain into a small bowl, add 2 tablespoons water and sprinkle over the gelatine. Leave to stand until the gelatine becomes spongy. Place the bowl over a pan of simmering water until the gelatine dissolves and the liquid is clear. Remove.</li>\r\n<li>Add the egg yolks to the bowl with the lemon zest and stir in the Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Caster Cane Sugar. Using an electric beater, whisk until thick and mousse-like. Pour over the warm gelatine and whisk together. Lightly whip the cream until soft peaks form then fold into the souffl&eacute; mixture. Refrigerate until it starts to thicken.</li>\r\n<li>Whisk the egg whites until they form soft peaks. Fold one large spoonful into the lemon mixture to lighten the texture then gently fold in the rest. Pour into the prepared dish or dishes and refrigerate until set.</li>\r\n<li>To remove the paper, remove the string and use the edge of a palette knife to ease the paper away from the souffl&eacute;. Place the knife behind the paper and gently pull the paper without pulling the souffl&eacute; .</li>\r\n<li>Dust with the Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar and scatter over the chopped nuts.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(260, NULL, NULL, 'Chilled LEMON SOUFFLÃ ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>For the Souffle</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>150g Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Caster Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>300ml double Cream&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>6 large eggs, separated</li>\r\n<li>3 unwaxed lemons</li>\r\n<li>15g sachet powdered gelatine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>to decorate</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Icing Cane Sugar, to dust</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp shelled pistachio nuts, finely chopped&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
