(287, NULL, NULL, 'TABLE', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table  ><colgroup><col  /> <col  /> <col width="161" /> <col  /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl24" >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl26" >Nutrition Values<br /> &nbsp;per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl26" width="161">Women`s GDA per serving</td>\r\n<td class="xl25" >Typical GDA Values (Women)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25" >Energy (kcal)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">73</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">4%&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl29" > 2000 kcal</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Energy (kJ)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">309</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">N/A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25" >Protein (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.5</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">1%</td>\r\n<td class="xl29" > 45g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25" >Carbohydrates (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">18</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">8%</td>\r\n<td class="xl29" > 230g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25" >of which sugars (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">16.7</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">19%</td>\r\n<td class="xl29" > 90g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25" >Fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0.1</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl29" > 70g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25" >Of which saturated fat (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl29" > 20g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Fibre (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl28">0.3</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">1%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">24g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="xl25">Salt (g)</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">0</td>\r\n<td class="xl27">0%</td>\r\n<td class="xl24">6g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(288, NULL, NULL, 'Italian Hot Chocolate Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li class="step-1">Break the chocolate into pieces, pop in a processor and, using the pulse button, whizz until the chocolate is finely chopped. Tip the chocolate into a pan along with water, milk and&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Light at Heart Brown&nbsp;and slowly bring to the boil. Whisk the mixture constantly to prevent the chocolate from burning.</li>\r\n<li class="step-2">When the hot chocolate mix is simmering remove the pan from the heat. Then, using a hand held blender, carefully blitz until frothy. Pour into glass mugs to serve.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4 class="ir">GET THE KIDS INVOLVED:</h4>\r\n<p>Once the hot chocolate has been carefully poured into cups, let the children have fun by squirting light real cream from an aerosol on top!</p>\r\n<h4 class="ir">TIP:</h4>\r\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t have a hand held (stick) blender just whisk well with a traditional balloon whisk instead. For ultimate presentation, add a sprinkling of chocolate curls on top just before serving.</p>', NULL),
(289, NULL, NULL, 'Italian Hot Chocolate Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li class="lah">1 tbsp (or to taste)&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Light at Heart Brown&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>125g dark cooks'' chocolate, 72% cocoa solids</li>\r\n<li>200ml cold water</li>\r\n<li>500ml skimmed milk</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(290, NULL, NULL, 'Italian Hot Chocolate Nutritional Information', 1, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<table >\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Values per serving</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Women`s GDA per serving</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Typical GDA Values (Women)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Energy (kcal)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>653</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>8%&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>2000 kcal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Energy (kJ)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>156</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>N/A</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Protein (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>4.5</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>10%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>45g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Carbohydrates (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>13</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>6%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>230g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>of which sugars (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>12.1</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>13%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>90g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Fat (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>9.8</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>14%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>70g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Of which saturated fat (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>5.8</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>29%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n\r\n<p>20g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Fibre (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>2.3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>10%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>24g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >\r\n<p><strong>Salt (g)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>0.09</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>2%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>6g</p>\r\n\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL),
(291, NULL, NULL, 'METHOD', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Trim, halve, core and deseed the red peppers, then roughly chop. Pop in a large heavy based pan (or preserving pan) with the chopped onions and stir in the vinegar and salt. Add the freshly ground black pepper with the fennel seeds and onion seeds.</li>\r\n<li>Mix well and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat and simmer until the vegetables are tender (this takes about 30-40 minutes but depends on the size of the pepper pieces) stirring frequently. Add the&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Light at Heart White, reduce the heat and stir until completely dissolved. Then turn up the heat and simmer for 30-40 minutes until the relish has thickened and reduced (stir every so often to stop it sticking). Spoon into warm, sterilised jars and cover with a small disc of waxed paper, or cute gingham-patterned fabric and ribbons for that homemade feel. Leave to cool and then store in the fridge.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4>GET THE KIDS INVOLVED:</h4>\r\n<p>For a charming touch, get the kids to write out - and stick on - the jar labels.</p>\r\n<h4>TIP:</h4>\r\n<p>Don&rsquo;t skimp on the salt as it helps balance the mix of&nbsp;Light at Heart and vinegar. To sterilise the jars we recommend placing them in the dishwasher on the hottest setting. Once finished place on a wooden board facing upwards, before placing the jars in a pre-heated oven at 180&deg;C/Fan160&deg;C/Gas mark 4, until all moisture is removed.&nbsp;</p>', NULL),
(292, NULL, NULL, 'INGREDIENTS', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>125g Tate &amp; Lyle Light at Heart White</li>\r\n<li>7 red peppers, weighing about 1kg</li>\r\n<li>3 red onions, weighing about 500g, trimmed, peeled and chopped</li>\r\n<li>500ml white wine vinegar</li>\r\n<li>a couple of generous pinches of sea salt</li>\r\n<li>a couple of generous twists of freshly ground black pepper</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp fennel seeds</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp black onion seeds</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
