(355, NULL, NULL, 'Lemon Biscuits Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol start="1">\r\n<li>Put the butter and sugar into a bowl, beat together until pale and creamy. Beat in the egg. And lemon zest. Sift in the flour and mix with a spoon until the mixture comes together. With floured hands, bring the dough together then turn onto a floured surface and knead until smooth.</li>\r\n<li>Dust the rolling pin with flour and roll to an even thickness about 5mm/&frac14; in. Using a pastry cutter about 6cm/2&frac12; inch diameter, cut out rounds and transfer them to 2 lightly buttered baking sheets. Refrigerate for 30 minutes</li>\r\n<li>Heat the oven to 170C/325F/gas mark 3 and bake the biscuits for 15 minutes or until very lightly browned. Remove from the oven and sprinkle with about 1 tsp of&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Fruit Sugar.</li>\r\n<li>Transfer to a wire rack to cool.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL),
(356, NULL, NULL, 'Lemon Biscuits', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>110g/4oz butter</li>\r\n<li>75g/3oz Tate &amp; Lyle Fruit Sugar</li>\r\n<li>1 medium egg</li>\r\n<li>finely grated zest 1 large lemon</li>\r\n<li>225g/8oz plain flour</li>\r\n<li>a little extra sugar to sprinkle</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(357, NULL, NULL, 'Lemon Biscuits', 0, 'page', 0, 3, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', NULL, NULL),
(358, NULL, NULL, 'Gingerbread Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol start="1">\r\n<li>Grease and line with non-stick parchment a 23cm/9ins square cake tin. Heat the oven to 170C/325F/gas mark 3.</li>\r\n<li>Put the butter,&nbsp;Tate &amp; Lyle Fruit Sugar&nbsp;and Lyle''s Black Treacle into a small pan and set over a medium heat until the butter has melted. Stir until smooth and remove from the heat.</li>\r\n<li>Whisk the eggs and milk together. Sift the dry ingredients into a large bowl, add the melted mixture and the eggs and beat to make a smooth batter.</li>\r\n<li>Pour into the prepared tin and level. Bake in the oven for 45-50 minutes or until firm to the touch and a skewer comes out clean when tested.</li>\r\n<li>Leave in the tin to cool for 10 minutes, then turn onto a wire rack to cool completely. The cake can be cut into squares, or bars or thick slices.<span style="font-size: 1em;">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4>TIP:</h4>\r\n<p>This cake can be iced using 225g/8oz Tate &amp; Lyle Icing Sugar mixed with lemon juice until&nbsp;smooth</p>', NULL),
(359, NULL, NULL, 'Gingerbread Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ul>\r\n<li>110g/4oz butter</li>\r\n<li>150g/5oz Tate &amp; Lyle Fruit Sugar</li>\r\n<li>4 level tbsp Lyle''s Black Treacle</li>\r\n<li>2 large eggs</li>\r\n<li>150ml/&frac14; pt milk</li>\r\n<li>300g/10oz plain flour</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp baking powder</li>\r\n<li>&frac12; tsp bicarbonate of soda</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp ground ginger</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
