(387, NULL, NULL, 'Miss Cakehead', 1, 'page', 1, 5, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<p>I was so excited to be asked to work on the &ldquo;Tasting House&rdquo; project &ndash; as &lsquo;Miss Cakehead&rsquo; was born out of the Cake Britain event for Tate &amp; Lyle Sugars back in 2010. As you can imagine it was fairly daunting to be given four weeks, a range of 8 new sugars, and challenged to help create a series of edible rooms themed around them. But being the only &lsquo;curator of cake&rsquo; in the World I was up for the challenge!&nbsp;</p>', NULL),
(388, NULL, NULL, 'The challenge', 1, 'page', 1, 0, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<p>I was so excited to be asked to work on the &ldquo;Tasting House&rdquo; project &ndash; as &lsquo;Miss Cakehead&rsquo; was born out of the Cake Britain event for Tate &amp; Lyle Sugars back in 2010. As you can imagine it was fairly daunting to be given four weeks, a range of 8 new sugars, and challenged to help create a series of edible rooms themed around them. But being the only &lsquo;curator of cake&rsquo; in the World I was up for the challenge!&nbsp;</p>', NULL),
(389, NULL, NULL, 'Toffe Pudding Instructions', 1, 'page', 0, 1, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<ol>\r\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/Fan160&deg;C, 350&deg;F, Gas 4.</li>\r\n<li>Grease and line a 20-23cm/8-9&rdquo; square shallow cake tin.</li>\r\n<li>Put the dates into a pan with 250ml water, bring to the boil then lower the heat and simmer 2 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir in the bicarbonate of soda.</li>\r\n<li>Beat the butter and Tate &amp; Lyle Soft Brown Cane Sugar with the Lyle&rsquo;s Black Treacle until soft and creamy, then beat in the vanilla extract and eggs.</li>\r\n<li>Fold in the flour and dates with their liquid and mix well to give a soft consistency. Turn into the prepared tin and bake for 30-40 minutes or until a skewer comes out clean.</li>\r\n<li>Meanwhile put all the ingredients for the toffee sauce into a pan and stir together over a low heat until the Tate &amp; Lyle Light Soft Brown Cane Sugar has dissolved.</li>\r\n<li>Cut the pudding into portions and serve with the warm toffee sauce poured over.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL),
(390, NULL, NULL, 'Ingredients', 1, 'page', 0, 2, NULL, 'twelve', NULL, NULL, 'html', '<h4>For the pudding</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>175g (6oz) moist stoned dates, roughly chopped</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp bicarbonate of soda</li>\r\n<li>75g (3oz) butter</li>\r\n<li>175g (6oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Light Soft Brown Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp Lyle&rsquo;s Black Treacle</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li>\r\n<li>2 large eggs</li>\r\n<li>175g (6oz) self-raising flour</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>For the toffee sauce</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>75g (3oz) butter</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp Lyle&rsquo;s Golden Syrup</li>\r\n<li>175g (6oz) Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Light Soft Brown Cane Sugar</li>\r\n<li>150ml (5floz) double cream&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
