(1, 1, NULL, NULL, '2013-01-22', 'Filtered Product Results', 'tagged', 99, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'original', NULL, 'product_filtered_list', NULL, NULL, 'Medium <br> bodied buttery', 0, 0, 54, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 0),
(4, 1, 16, 59, '2013-01-31', 'Explore Our Range', 'list', 6, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Explore Our Range</p>', 'original', 'noBgcolor', 'product_home', '<p>Tate &amp; Lyle sugars are made from 100% sugar cane naturally grown in the sunshine, and have been for over 130 years. We are proud to continue to provide delightful sweet satisfaction to consumers around the world.&nbsp;When you buy Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade cane sugar, you help us to help over 20,000 small scale cane farmers in developing countries. To find out more,&nbsp;<a href="/we-are-fairtrade">click here</a>.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'Medium <br /> bodied buttery', NULL, NULL, 53, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 0),
(5, 1, NULL, NULL, '2013-02-26', 'Taste Experience', 'taste-experience', 99, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_cat_page', '<p>A Journey of Taste:&nbsp;Discover a delicious new world in the baking with our range of distinctly different flavours of brown and golden cane sugars inspired by sugar cane producing regions across the globe. Each sugar has unique characteristics which maximise the individual flavour profiles and textures of your cooking and&nbsp;beverages.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'Medium <br /> bodied buttery', NULL, NULL, 58, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 0),
(6, 1, NULL, NULL, '2013-02-26', 'Simply Sweetening', 'simply-sweetening', 99, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_cat_page', '<p>Tate &amp; Lyle sugars are made from 100% sugar cane naturally grown in the sunshine, and have been for over 130 years. We are proud to continue to provide delightful sweet satisfaction to consumers around the world.&nbsp;When you buy Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade cane sugar, you help us to help over 20,000 small scale cane farmers in developing countries. To find out more, <a href="/we-are-fairtrade">click here</a>.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'Your <br> kitchen staple', NULL, NULL, 55, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 19, 0),
(7, 1, NULL, NULL, '2013-02-26', 'Sugar Cubes', 'sugar-cubes', 99, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_cat_page', '<p>Convenience Squared. Tate &amp; Lyle Sugars founder, Henry Tate, introduced the sugar cube to the UK in 1875. Innovation has always been, and remains to this day, at the heart of our brand.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'Great <br> for coffee', NULL, NULL, 56, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 32, 0),
(8, 1, NULL, NULL, '2013-02-26', 'Better Balance', 'better-balance', 99, 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_cat_page', '<p>Want to use less but get the same great results? Whether you are looking for a natural solution to lower your calorie intake in both your drinks and cooking, or instead, you are seeking to sustain your blood sugar levels, then this range can help. Tate &amp; Lyle Sugars endeavors to create a better balance for you.</p>', NULL, 'Fancy something different?', NULL, NULL, 57, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 28, 0),
(11, 1, NULL, 160, '2013-03-08', 'Golden Caster Sugar', 'golden-caster-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'goldencaster', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p style="margin: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial;">The Mayan Journey is inspired by the colourful and mysterious land of the great Mayan people. Home to spectacular pyramids and temples, today the rich cultivated land provides some of the best sugar cane in the world. Golden Caster is a pale golden sugar with delicate honey flavour, evoking the sweet fairground candyfloss scent.&nbsp;Light Bodied Fine, Flavour Strength 1.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; text-align: justify; font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!--EndFragment-->', NULL, 'Mayan Inspired', 1, 1, 159, NULL, '05010115804894', '05010115804887', NULL, '325g', '700g', 161, NULL, 0),
(12, 1, NULL, 163, '2013-03-08', 'Golden Granulated Sugar', 'golden-granulated-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'goldengranul', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>The South Pacific journey is inspired by a thousand years of trading routes and cultivation of sugar cane on the sun drenched island nations in Melanesia. The Golden Granulated is a sparkling golden sugar with a shy aroma and subtle caramel. The sugar&rsquo;s gentle crunch enhances both taste and texture.&nbsp;Light Bodied Mellow, Flavour Strength 2.</p>', NULL, 'South Pacific Inspired', 1, 1, 162, NULL, '05010115804870', '05010115804863', NULL, '350g', '750g', 164, NULL, 1),
(13, 1, NULL, 166, '2013-03-08', 'Golden Syrup Sugar', 'golden-syrup-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'goldensyrup', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>The British journey is inspired by Abram Lyle, who in 1883 began refining on the river Thames banks. The unique flavour of golden syrup has been enjoyed around the world ever since. The Golden Syrup sugar is rich, bold and beautifully distinctive with a luscious, lingering sweetness.&nbsp;Medium Bodied Rich, Flavour Strength 3.</p>', NULL, 'British inspired', 1, 1, 165, NULL, '05010115803798', NULL, NULL, '325g', NULL, 167, NULL, 2),
(14, 1, NULL, 169, '2013-03-08', 'Demerara Sugar', 'demerara-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'demerara', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>The Guyanese journey is inspired by a 17th century cultivation&nbsp;on the banks of what is now known as the River Demerara. Ever since, the sugar cane fields have proliferated across Guyana. Demerara is a fruity, sweet-spiced sugar with large glassy amber crystals providing a distinctive textual crunch.&nbsp;Medium Bodied Fruity, Flavour Strength 3.</p>', NULL, 'Guyanese Inspired', 1, 1, 168, NULL, '05010115804856', '05010115804849', NULL, '350g', '750g', 170, NULL, 3),
(15, 1, NULL, 172, '2013-03-08', 'Light Muscovado Sugar', 'light-muscovado-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'lmuscovado', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>The Caribbean journey&nbsp;reflects the evolution of a sugar that honours&nbsp;Caribbean''s&nbsp;cane producing islands and their vibrant, colourful, diverse cultures and sunny disposition. Light Muscovado sugar has a creamy aromatic flavour, a warm honey colour and delightfully moist, crumbly texture.&nbsp;Medium Bodied Aromatic, Flavour Strength 4.</p>', NULL, 'Caribbean Inspired', 1, 1, 171, NULL, '05010115804993', NULL, NULL, '325g', NULL, 173, NULL, 5),
(16, 1, NULL, 175, '2013-03-08', 'Dark Muscovado Sugar', 'dark-muscovado-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'dmuscovado', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>The Barbadian journey celebrates the sticky intense dark sugars traditionally known as &lsquo;Barbados&rsquo; or &lsquo;Moist&rsquo; sugars that characterise this rich territory&rsquo;s contribution to cane sugar in the sunshine. Dark Muscovado sugar has a rich and aromatic flavour with a moist, fudgy texture.&nbsp;Full Bodied Rich, Flavour Strength 5.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'Barbados Inspired', 1, 1, 174, NULL, '05010115804955', NULL, NULL, '325', NULL, 176, NULL, 7),
(17, 1, NULL, 178, '2013-03-08', 'Light Soft Brown Sugar', 'light-soft-brown-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'lsofbrown', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Inspired by centuries of trading sugars across turquoise seas into the sun drenched Mediterranean Peninsular. Mediterranean''s delectable pastries are defined by this subdued flavoured sugar. Light Soft Brown sugar is moist with fine, quick-dissolving crystals, ideal for sauces and fruity preserves. Medium Bodied Buttery, Flavour Strength 4.</p>', NULL, 'Mediterranean Inspired', 1, 1, 177, NULL, '05010115804917', '05010115804900', NULL, '325g', '700g', 179, NULL, 4),
(18, 1, NULL, 186, '2013-03-11', 'Dark Soft Brown Sugar', 'dark-soft-brown-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'dsofbrown', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Our Mississippi journey reflects the sugar cane farming tradition of the Deep South. Inspired by the greatest brown sugars that help create the rich, sweet and big tastes of soulful southern cooking, Dark Soft Brown sugar has a toasted, malty flavour with a hint of savouriness and a moist texture that melts easily. Full Bodied Velvet, Flavour Strength 5.</p>', NULL, 'Mississippi inspired', 1, 1, 185, NULL, '05010115804931', '05010115804924', NULL, '325g', '700g', 187, NULL, 6),
(19, 1, NULL, 189, '2013-03-11', 'Granulated Sugar', 'granulated-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'granulated', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Across the generations we are proud to have played a small part in so many great British cuppas. Did you know tea breaks are traditions that have been with us for over 200 years?</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively try our&nbsp;<a title="Golden Granulated Sugar" href="/product/golden-granulated-sugar">Golden Granulated sugar</a>&nbsp;for more flavor in your tea.</p>', '2kg', 'PERFECT FOR TEA', 1, 1, 188, NULL, '05010115926404', '05010115926404', '05010115927142', '500g', '1kg', 190, NULL, 8),
(20, 1, NULL, 192, '2013-03-11', 'Caster Sugar', 'caster-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'castersugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Our Caster Sugar is perfect for baking, blending easily to ensure smooth results. Its superfine crystals blend into the mixture produce and guarantee great results every time. Did you know the Victoria Sponge was named after our very own Queen Vic.&nbsp;</p>', '2kg', 'A PIECE OF CAKE', 1, 1, 191, NULL, '05010115926985', '05010115926978', '05010115926992', '500g', '1kg', 193, NULL, 9),
(21, 1, NULL, 195, '2013-03-11', 'Icing Sugar', 'icing-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'icingsugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Essential for making glac&eacute; or butter cream icing. Simply mix with water to produce a glossy &ldquo;glac&eacute;&rdquo; icing perfect for any size cake. For butter cream icing simply cream the soft butter first. For special occasion cakes, reach for the <a title="Royal Icing Sugar" href="/product/royal-icing-sugar">Royal Icing</a> for piped and firmer results.&nbsp;Did you know the word cake has origins in the Old Norse language of the Vikings?</p>', NULL, 'FOR THAT FINISHING TOUCH', 1, 1, 194, NULL, '05010115927166', '05010115927159', NULL, '500g', '1kg', 196, NULL, 10),
(22, 1, NULL, 198, '2013-03-11', 'Royal Icing Sugar', 'royal-icing-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'royalicing', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Ideal for traditional hard set decoration icing, flat icing, or as a softer icing. If you are creating a Wedding or Christmas cake masterpiece then this is the right icing for you. Our tip is to add egg whites to ensure a firm set to the icing on your cakes. Did you know the wedding cake became white when Queen Victoria chose to wear white at her wedding?</p>', NULL, 'A CLASSIC FINISH', 1, 1, 197, NULL, '05010115927180', NULL, NULL, '500g', NULL, 199, NULL, 11),
(23, 1, NULL, 201, '2013-03-11', 'Fondant Icing Sugar', 'fondant-icing-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'fondant', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Ideal for giving a soft and glossy finish to sponge cakes, French fancies and is also excellent for sugar-modelling. Our tip is to add glucose syrup to ensure a softer set. Did you know Anna Maria Russell, Duchess of Bedford, a friend of Queen Victoria started the British tradition of "afternoon tea"?</p>', NULL, 'A FANCY FINISH', 1, 1, 200, NULL, '05010115924691', NULL, NULL, '500g', NULL, 202, NULL, 12),
(24, 1, NULL, 204, '2013-03-11', 'Jam Sugar', 'jam-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'jamsugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Sugar is vital in jams as a natural preserving agent and flavouring. Added pectin helps ensure a perfect set when using low pectin fruits like strawberries or cherries.&nbsp;Did you know it is thought that some of the first jams were produced in the Middle East?</p>', NULL, 'SPREAD THE LOVE', 1, 1, 203, NULL, '05010115926831', NULL, NULL, '1kg', NULL, 205, NULL, 13),
(25, 1, NULL, 207, '2013-03-11', 'Pectin Sachets', 'pectin-sachets', 99, 1, 1, 'pectin', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Perfect for home-made jams and jellies made with soft fruits. Mix one sachet of Pectin with 1kg of Tate &amp; Lyle Fairtrade Granulated sugar, a squeeze of lemon juice'', and the fruit of your choice.Did you know apples and citrus fruits are naturally high in pectin whereas soft fruits like cherries and strawberries contain only smaller amounts?</p>', NULL, 'SET TO IMPRESS', 0, 1, 206, NULL, '05010115927906', NULL, NULL, '3x8g', NULL, 208, NULL, 14),
(26, 1, NULL, 210, '2013-03-11', 'Preserving Sugar', 'preserving-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'preserving', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Oranges, grapefruit and citrus fruit &ndash; make marmalade! Larger, slower dissolving crystals reduce stirring, prevent burning, and produce less froth during boiling. There&rsquo;s no added pectin, so it&rsquo;s best used with fruits containing high pectin levels. Did you know the great city of Dundee gains the accolade as the city best known for Marmalade in the UK?</p>', NULL, 'BEST DRESSED TOAST', 1, 1, 209, NULL, '05010115927173', NULL, NULL, '1kg', NULL, 211, NULL, 15),
(27, 1, NULL, 213, '2013-03-11', 'Fruit Sugar', 'fruit-sugar', 99, 1, 1, 'fruitsugar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Fruit sugar, or fructose, is sweeter than standard sugar and has a low Glycaemic Index of 23, helping you to sustain steady sugar levels and feel full for longer. It is absorbed much slower than glucose by the body, giving a slow release of energy over a longer period of time.</p>', NULL, 'Helps you to sustain', 0, 1, 212, NULL, '5010115915309', NULL, NULL, '250g', NULL, 214, NULL, 22),
(28, 1, NULL, 216, '2013-03-11', 'Light At HeartÂ® White Sugar & Stevia Blend', 'light-at-heart-white-sugar-stevia-blend', 99, 1, 1, 'lahwhite', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Light at Heart&reg;&nbsp;White is not simply a Stevia based sweetener but the perfect blend of granulated cane sugar and Stevia leaf extract. It''s free from artificial ingredients and being twice as sweet as standard sugar, you only have to add half as much to cut calories by 50%. Stevia is 100% natural, tastes sweet like sugar, but contains no calories.&nbsp;<a title="FAQs L@H" href="/faq#heartFaq">Find out more about Stevia</a>.</p>', NULL, 'Great taste naturally', 0, 1, 215, NULL, '5010115948543', NULL, NULL, '450g', NULL, 217, NULL, 21),
(29, 1, NULL, 219, '2013-03-11', 'Light at HeartÂ® Brown Sugar & Stevia Blend', 'light-at-heart-brown-sugar-stevia-blend', 99, 1, 1, 'lahbrown', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Light at Heart&reg; Brown is a perfect blend of Demerara pure cane sugar and Stevia leaf extract: free from artificial ingredients and twice as sweet as standard sugar, you only have to add half as much to cut calories by 50%. Cooking with Light at Heart is simple and gives you the same taste as when using regular sugar but with fewer calories.&nbsp;<a title="FAQs L@H" href="/faq#heartFaq">Find out more about Stevia</a>.</p>', NULL, 'Naturally versatile', 0, 1, 218, NULL, '5010115948550', NULL, NULL, '450g', NULL, 220, NULL, 20),
(30, 1, NULL, 222, '2013-03-11', 'White Sugar Cubes', 'white-sugar-cubes', 99, 1, 1, 'whitecubes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Across the generations we are proud to have played a part in so many great British cuppas.&nbsp;Did you know that in 1875 Henry Tate bought the rights to technology enabling him to introduce sugar cubes to the UK? For a deeper flavour in your coffee, enjoy our <a title="Demerara Sugar Cubes" href="/product/demerara-sugar-cubes">Demerara sugar cubes</a>.</p>', NULL, 'Tea time', 1, 1, 221, NULL, '05010115934621', NULL, NULL, '500g', NULL, 223, NULL, 18),
(31, 1, NULL, 225, '2013-03-11', 'White Rough Cut Sugar Cubes', 'white-rough-cut-sugar-cubes', 99, 1, 1, 'whiteroughcubes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Enjoy with afternoon tea, the clean sweet taste of cane sugar grown in the sunshine. Did you know that tea has similar geographical origins in South East Asia to that of sugar cane? The wife of Charles II is said to have been a key proponent in establishing tea drinking in England. For a deeper flavour in your coffee, enjoy our <a title="Demerara Sugar Cubes" href="/product/demerara-sugar-cubes">Demerara sugar cubes</a>.</p>', NULL, 'Tea time', 1, 1, 224, NULL, '05010115934393', NULL, NULL, '500g', NULL, 226, NULL, 19),
(32, 1, NULL, 228, '2013-03-11', 'Demerara Sugar Cubes', 'demerara-sugar-cubes', 99, 1, 1, 'demeraracubes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Add the fruity, sweet-spiced molasses taste of brown cane sugar to your favourite cup of coffee. Did you know that in 1674 the Women&rsquo;s Petition Against Coffee was launched to curtail their husbands from frequenting coffee houses, citing their failure to attend to duties at home? For a&nbsp;clean&nbsp;sweet taste in your tea, enjoy our&nbsp;<a title="White Sugar Cubes" href="/product/white-sugar-cubes">White sugar cubes</a>.</p>', NULL, 'Kick back with a coffee', 1, 1, 227, NULL, '05010115934638', NULL, NULL, '500g', NULL, 229, NULL, 16),
(33, 1, NULL, 231, '2013-03-11', 'Demerara Rough Cut Sugar Cubes', 'demerara-rough-cut-sugar-cubes', 99, 1, 1, 'demerararoughcubes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'product_article', '<p>Enjoy in your coffee the fruity and subtle spicy flavour that only comes from sugar cane grown in the sunshine. Did you know the first known coffee house in London was established in 1652, following on from the Oxford Style coffee house famed for their scholarly debate? For a sweet taste in your tea, enjoy our&nbsp;<a title="White Rough Cut Sugar" href="/product/white-rough-cut-sugar-cubes">White Rough Cut sugar cubes</a>.</p>', NULL, 'Coffee time', 1, 1, 230, NULL, '05010115934607', NULL, NULL, '500g', NULL, 232, NULL, 17);
